**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:

As asked on forum: https://discuss.elastic.co/t/continous-transforms-accumulating-delay-can-be-tweak-for-speed-up/239807/6

Transforms don't use last checkpoint date on date range calculation when we use differents fields on timestamp aggregation and on sync transforms setting.

**Steps to reproduce**:

On source index, create two time fields : 

- @timestamp => The date of the creation on the log on nginx
- processed_at => The date of processing the log, added by the ingest (logstash on my case)

Create a continuous transform like this : 

```
{  
  "settings": {
    "max_page_search_size": 10000
  },
  "frequency": "60s",
  "id": "THE_ID",
  "source": {
    "index": [
      "source-*"
    ],
    "query": {
      "bool": {
        "filter": [
          {
             // filter of transform
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "destination-index"
  },
  "sync": {
    "time": {
      "field": "processed_at",
      "delay": "5m"
    }
  },
  "pivot": {
    "group_by": {
      "@timestamp": {
        "date_histogram": {
          "field": "@timestamp",
          "calendar_interval": "1h"
        }
      },
      // some other group by
    },
    "aggregations": {
      // some aggregation settings
    }
  }
}
```

On each checkpoint transform query all index instead of range between old and current checkpoint.

**Provide logs (if relevant)**:

`range\":{\"processed_at\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":1594027879901
`

If a `date_histo` is specified with a script, no field, and a "mismatched" `value_type` you can hit an NPE when trying to generate an exception text.  This happens because we try to lookup the field context to make a useful exception text... but there is no field here thus NPE.  :)

Edit: I think this probably applies to any agg that accepts a script, I just stumbled into it while investigating a date_histo thing

Reproduction:

```
PUT test/
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "timestamp": {
        "type": "date"
      }
    }
  }
}

GET test/_search
{
  "aggs": {
    "the_histo": {
      "date_histogram": {
        "script": {
          "source": "return 123",
          "lang": "painless"
        },
        "value_type": "string",
        "interval": "1d"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Caused by: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/master/server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/search/aggregations/support/ValuesSourceRegistry.java#L135

Perhaps more interesting, if you do supply a field we find the field context and then throw a confusing exception:

`"Field [timestamp] of type [date] is not supported for aggregation [date_histogram]"`

I think we need to include `value_type` in the exception message somewhere, so that it's clear that was part of the reason we couldn't find an aggregator.

