**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:
Just updated from 7.7 to 7.8 and changed the `Kibana` config to use the `kibana_system` user instead of `kibana`, as described in [BreakingChanges](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/breaking-changes-7.8.html#builtin-users-changes). Unfortunately afterwards `Kibana` can no longer authenticate to `Elasticsearch`. I had to explicitly set the password for `kibana_system` to the one of `kibana` to make it work again.

Please update the release docs to clearly state that the password for `kibana_system` must be set explicitly. The current description of "user was `renamed`" implies that the existing password would be preserved, which is not the case.

